&lt;p&gt;The information provided on this website is for general informational purposes only. While we strive to keep the information accurate and up to date, we make no representations or warranties of any kind, express or implied, about the completeness, accuracy, reliability, suitability, or availability with respect to the website or the information, products, services, or related graphics contained on the website for any purpose. Any reliance you place on such information is therefore strictly at your own risk.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Philosophy</title><link>https://devil-engineering.de/philosophy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 05 Apr 2021 20:50:44 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://devil-engineering.de/philosophy/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;With over 25 years of experience in enterprise software development, I work as a freelance Cloud Engineer and DevOps specialist — helping teams design and operate reliable systems on modern cloud infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continuous improvement shapes how I work. Cloud computing, infrastructure automation, and DevOps practices evolve quickly, and keeping pace with relevant developments is what separates solutions that hold up in production from those that become technical debt.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before designing anything, I invest time in understanding the client&amp;rsquo;s technical context, business constraints, and the actual problem being solved. Generic architectures rarely fit specific situations well — the goal is always something that creates measurable value, not just something that looks good on paper.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Publications</title><link>https://devil-engineering.de/publications/</link><pubDate>Mon, 05 Apr 2021 20:50:44 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://devil-engineering.de/publications/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A selection of open-source contributions, tools, and talks from the past years.&lt;/p&gt;
